    "1": ("Let's start off from the basics \n"
          "Adding 3 numbers together \n"
          "======================================= \n" 
          "Remember these 3 points: \n"
          "1: Start from left to right\n"
          "2: Add the first 2 numbers\n"
          "3: Add the result to the third number\n"
          "======================================== \n\n"
          
          "Subtracting 3 numbers together \n"
          "======================================= \n" 
          "Remember these 3 points: \n"
          "1: Start from left to right\n"
          "2: Minus the first 2 numbers\n"
          "3: Minus the result to the third number\n"
          "======================================== \n\n"

        "Ever wondered what's the relation between addition and subtraction? \n"
        "Addtions and Subtractions are the opposite of each other"
        "Let me show you with example: \n"
        " 1 + 2 + 4  = 7 \n"
        " 1 + 2 = 7 - 4 \n"
        " 3 = 3 \n"
        "Did you notice the 4 is brought over to the right side and the sign became - ?\n"
    
        "\nLet's try with the another example: \n"
        " 10 - 2 - 5  = 3\n"
        " 10 - 2 = 3 + 5 \n"
        " 8 = 8 \n"
        "Did you notice the 5 is brought over to the right side and the sign became + ?\n"
        "I hope you got the hook of it ;) \n\n" 

        "Lets now move on to Multiplication of 3 numbers \n"
        "======================================= \n" 
        "Remember these 3 points: \n"
        "1: Start from left to right\n"
        "2: Multiply the first 2 numbers\n"
        "3: Multiply the result to the third number\n"
        "======================================== \n\n"

        "Division of 3 numbers \n"
        "======================================= \n" 
        "Remember these 3 points: \n"
        "1: Start from left to right\n"
        "2: Divide the first 2 numbers\n"
        "3: Divide the result to the third number\n"
        "======================================== \n\n"

        "Similar to addition and subtraction, there is a relation between division and multiplication? \n"
        "Division and Multiplication are the opposite of each other \n"
        "Let me show you with example: \n"
        " 1 x 2 x 3  = 6 \n"
        " 1 x 2 = 6 / 3 \n"
        " 2 = 2 \n"
        "Did you notice the 3 is brought over to the right side and the sign became / ? \n"
        "\nLet's try with the another example: \n"
